with pytest.warns(RepeatElementWarning, match=
    '.*same elements in the given data'):
    a = IndexCollection([1, 2, 2, 3])
with pytest.warns(RepeatElementWarning, match=
    '.*has already in the collection.*'):
    a.add(3)
a.add(4)
with pytest.warns(InexistentElementWarning, match=
    '.*to discard is not in the collection.*'):
    a.discard(6)
assert a.pop() == 4
with pytest.warns(RepeatElementWarning, match=
    '.*has already in the collection.*'):
    a.update(IndexCollection([2, 9, 10]))
with pytest.warns(InexistentElementWarning, match=
    '.*to discard is not in the collection.*'):
    a.difference_update(IndexCollection([2, 100]))
